    AcceptanceOmegaDD, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<AcceptanceStreettDD.StreettPairDD>, java.util.Collection<AcceptanceStreettDD.StreettPairDD>, java.util.List<AcceptanceStreettDD.StreettPairDD>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class AcceptanceStreettDD
extends java.util.ArrayList<AcceptanceStreettDD.StreettPairDD>
implements AcceptanceOmegaDD
    A Streett acceptance condition (based on JDD state sets). This is a list of StreettPairs, which can be manipulated with the usual List interface.
    Semantics: Each Streett pair has a state set R and G and is accepting iff visiting R infinitely often implies visiting G infinitely often: (G F "R") -> (G F "G"). The Streett condition is accepting if all pairs are accepting.
